post_text: Our teachers, paraprofessionals and other support staff have been working tirelessly to create high-quality in-person and remote learning options for our students. This has not been easy, but our staff is relentless in doing what is best for students. Parents, if you get a chance, please send a note or email to our teachers and support staff letting them know how much you appreciate what they are doing. It really does make a difference!

post_text:
These 3 GHMS teachers had some fun kicking off the new year this morning! Apparently they can't "mask" their excitement (they really are smiling behind those masks! ) to be starting this unique school year... also the year they retire!
Mrs. Wilmarth, Mrs. Anderson, and Mrs. Marks will reign as queens in the middle school this year! (No special treatment, but wear the crown proudly, ladies! You've earned it!). Please notice the face masks, shields, gloves, and "scepters" designed to remind students to socially distance.

post_text: Hello, Warriors! It's a beautiful day, so your teachers hope you're getting outside to play, just not with friends who don't live in your home! Today is the LAST day of our Spirit Week that we started last Tuesday. It's "Mindful Monday"! While you're enjoying that fresh air, Be thinking of this week and your remote learning. Check in every day by logging onto your drive and checking your email for important information from your teachers. We're VERY proud of all our students! Remember, Warriors are #alonetogether until we're together again! Warrior Covid-19 2020 Remote Learners

post_text: Beginning Tuesday, April 14th (no school on Monday the 13th), Germantown Hills School District will deliver lunches to any student whose parent makes a request regardless of whether they qualify for free or reduced price lunch. Again, any parent who wants lunch for their child(ren) may request lunch to be delivered. Lunches for the week are delivered on the first day of the week. If you would like to have lunch for you child(ren), please email Kim Kiesewetter, Food Service Director, at kiesewetterk@ghills69.com by noon on Thursday, April 9th.

Metamora Police Department
December 20, 2019 at 3:36 AM ·

Today was a very special day for one young man. Metamora HS student Ben Garza graduated high school today. Ben has always had a love for police. Today Officer Ian Cummings presented Ben with his very own Metamora Police uniform shirt, making Officer Garza an official honorary member of the Metamora Police Department. Afterward Officer Cummings and Garza went out on their first patrol in the squad car. Congratulations Officer Garza & thank you for letting us be apart of your day!! Also a big shout out and thank you to Cara Fletcher for taking these amazing photos!! 🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸🚓🚔🚓🚔🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸

post_text:
Today, our 5th-8th graders along with 5th-8th graders from Riverview Grade School had the honor and privilege to hear from Mr. Steen Metz, a Holocaust survivor. Mr. Metz's presentation was extremely powerful. Our students, who will be the last generation to have the opportunity to hear a first hand account of the Holocaust from a survivor, were amazing and their questions were very thoughtful.

Also, we had one student place first and and two students tie for third in the White Rose Essay Contest sponsored by the Peoria Jewish Federation. Kinsey Ganson, who placed 1st, and Isabella Signa, who tied for third with Jaxon Hicks, had the opportunity to read their essays for Mr. Metz.

To learn more about Mr. Metz's story, please visit this website: http://www.steenmetzneverforget.com

post_text:
Thanks to the help and generosity of teachers, staff, parents, and students, the PE Department is proud to announce that our students raised over $6,000, which will help send over 12 Veterans to Washington D.C. on upcoming Greater Peoria Honor Flights! This year we had one student, Kindergartner Rohman Wells, raise $620 alone for Peoria Honor Flight. The winning class, who raised the most money and will be receiving a Pizza Party (TBA), is Mrs. Schaffer's class who raised $921. The highest raising junior high student was Tristen Garren with $120.
Thank You again for all of your support for this great cause!

post_text: Congratulations to GHMS Cross Country runners! Sam Moore & the entire Girls Varsity Team who qualified for the state meet in challenging conditions against a talented field. Sam ran to a 1st place finish in a time of 11:23. The girls varsity team of Katie Lalumandier, Brooke Ramsey, Annie Hilst, Olyvia Palacios, Kayla Alderson, and Audrey Heil placed FIVE runners in the top 20 for 1st place in Sectionals! Katie led the way with a 1st place finish in a time of 12:31. Brooke finished in 7th place, Annie in 13th, Olyvia 14th, and Audrey 20th. Your Warrior Cross Country team will compete at the state meet in Bloomington this Saturday. They'd LOVE to see you there cheering for them! Go, Running Warriors!

post_text: For almost two years, Illinois has operated with just a partial budget for education and a “stopgap” budget for most everything else, leading to cuts at local government entities, community service organizations and education agencies that support our families and communities. Even though education has been funded, schools and students still suffer due to the lack of certainty, inequitable funding and current unpaid bills from the state. Let’s work together to #PassILBudget.

Highlight of the season for the Germantown Hills 8th Grade Girls Basketball team:

"We were down 8 points to Fieldcrest at the start of the 4th quarter and slowly worked our way back into the game. With 7 seconds left we steal the inbound pass, dribble the length of the court through traffic, and my post, Alana Terry, finds Grace Tyra for a lay-up at the buzzer where she scores and gets fouled for the win!"

Highlight of the season for the Germantown Hills 8th Grade Girls Basketball team:

"We were down 8 points to Fieldcrest at the start of the 4th quarter and slowly worked our way back into the game. With 7 seconds left we steal the inbound pass, dribble the length of the court through traffic, and my post, Alana Terry, finds Grace Tyra for a lay-up at the buzzer where she scores and gets fouled for the win!"
